entries.title: Stunning aerial footage shows California highway underwater
entries.description: Thousands of Californians are grappling with flooding and power outages after high winds and record-setting rainfall battered the state. CNN National Correspondent Camila Bernal has more.

entries.title: Why Putin's New Year's address is different than others
entries.description: CNN's Clare Sebastian reports that Russian President Vladimir Putin's 2023 New Year's address was very different from previous years, while retired Air Force Col. Cedric Leighton says Putin is continuing to push a false narrative about the war in Ukraine.

entries.title: Retired colonel predicts Putin's strategy in 2023
entries.description: Retired Air Force Col. Cedric Leighton predicts that Russian President Vladimir Putin is going to redouble attacks on Ukraine civilian infrastructure with the hope of reaching a stalemate in the war.

entries.title: Comedian who impersonated Barbara Walters pays tribute to her
entries.description: "Saturday Night Live" alum Cheri Oteri, known for her iconic Barbara Walters impersonation, pays tribute to the late broadcaster who passed away at the age of 93.

entries.title: TikTok is 'digital fentanyl,' incoming GOP China committee chair says
entries.description: TikTok is an addictive drug China's government is providing to Americans, says the incoming chairman of a new House select committee on China.

entries.title: Lula da Silva to be sworn in as Brazil's president, amid fears of violence from Bolsonaro supporters
entries.description: Luiz Inácio "Lula" da Silva was due to be sworn in as Brazil's new president on Sunday, as threats of violence loomed from supporters of his predecessor, Jair Bolsonaro.

entries.title: Watch chef make stunning art out of desserts inside this hotel kitchen
entries.description: French pastry chef Nicolas Guercio shows CNN's Paris correspondent Melissa Bell how he makes amazing works of art out of sugar.

entries.title: A skier died in an avalanche outside a Colorado resort
entries.description: A man died while skiing with his father in Colorado on Saturday when an avalanche struck and engulfed them both, a rescue team statement said.

entries.title: Kinzinger: I 'fear for the future of this country' if Trump isn't charged over Jan. 6
entries.description: Outgoing Republican Rep. Adam Kinzinger said Sunday he fears for the future of the country if former President Donald Trump isn't charged with a crime related to the January 6, 2021, attack on the US Capitol, though he believes the Justice Department will "do the right thing."

entries.title: 'Kaleidoscope' adds color to a bland heist story with a you-pick-the-order format
entries.description: The puzzle-like gimmick at the heart of "Kaleidoscope" -- watch the episodes in any order that you want -- can't conceal how otherwise uninspired this "Ocean's Eleven"-esque heist series actually is. Chalk that up in part to stiffly written characters, familiar situations and drawn-out logistical sequences. It's moderately watchable, but all told, color me unimpressed.

entries.title: Bash asks Kinzinger if Trump will be charged for Jan. 6. Hear his response
entries.description: Outgoing Rep. Adam Kinzinger (R-IL), who served on The House select committee investigating January 6, discusses whether he thinks former President Donald Trump will be charged for the insurrection on the Capitol.

entries.title: Modest Mouse drummer Jeremiah Green dead at 45
entries.description: Just days after his cancer diagnosis was publicly announced, Jeremiah Green -- the drummer for the rock band Modest Mouse -- has died, according to statements from his mother and bandmates.

entries.title: Canada is banning some foreigners from buying property after home prices surged
entries.description: Canada in 2023 is closing its doors to foreign investors who want to purchase homes.

entries.title: Running an errand on New Year's Day? Here is what's open and closed
entries.description: Many of us will close out 2022 with celebrations that stretch well into the wee hours of New Year's Day.

entries.title: Suspect in the Idaho college student killings plans to waive extradition hearing, attorney says
entries.description: The suspect in the killings of four University of Idaho college students plans to waive his extradition hearing this week, his attorney said, to expedite his return to the Gem State, where he faces four counts of first-degree murder.

entries.title: Meet the 18 contributors who think they know what will happen in 2023
entries.description: Predicting the future is impossible, and yet someone has to do it: in our case, the 18 contributors who take part in CNN Opinion's annual Crystal Ball feature. This time, they're making political, cultural, economic and sports-related predictions about the year ahead.

entries.title: Nine suffocate to death in Uganda New Year's firework crush
entries.description: At least nine people, including a 10-year-old boy, suffocated to death as crowds rushing to see a New Year's firework display got stuck in a narrow corridor in a shopping mall near Uganda's capital, police said.

entries.title: Former Pope Benedict XVI asked for forgiveness in a final letter published after his death
entries.description: Opinion: Benedict was more than 'God's Rottweiler' | People we lost in 2022 | Alisyn Camerota: What I wish I'd said to Barbara Walters

entries.title: Disgusting mystery shots make Anderson Cooper and Andy Cohen gag on live TV
entries.description: Anderson Cooper and Andy Cohen hosted CNN's New Year's Eve celebration and took non-alcoholic mystery shots at the top of each hour.

entries.title: Real Madrid star Vinícius Jr. says LaLiga 'doing nothing' over racist abuse
entries.description: Real Madrid forward Vinícius Jr. accused LaLiga of "doing nothing" about racism at matches after the Brazil star appeared to be racially abused during Real's 2-0 win at Real Valladolid on Friday.

entries.title: A pregnant mom crossed the Rio Grande decades ago to give her unborn child a better life. Now her daughter is becoming a member of Congress
entries.description: Delia Ramirez walks toward the microphone determined to make her message heard.

entries.title: This wildlife rehabilitator rescued over 1,600 bats during Houston cold snap
entries.description: A Texas wildlife rehabilitator nursed over 1,600 frozen bats back to health in her attic after many of them fell from their roosts during Houston's plunging temperatures last week.

entries.title: 5 science-based strategies for nailing your New Year's resolutions
entries.description: It's that time of year again. Champagne bottles have been popped, balls have dropped, and now your friends, family and colleagues are starting to ask, "What's your New Year's resolution?"

entries.title: This Ukrainian bakery prepares special bread for frontline soldiers
entries.description: A bakery in Bucha, Ukraine, prepares a special treat for soldiers on the front line. CNN senior international correspondent Ben Wedeman reports on the bread-making process.

entries.title: Inflation is killing the first dinner date
entries.description: Singles are ditching pricey white tablecloth meals for romance in the park or on a walk instead.

entries.title: 1 killed, at least 9 others injured in New Year's Eve shooting in Alabama
entries.description: One person was killed and nine others were injured in a shooting in Mobile, Alabama, Saturday night, just blocks from where people had gathered for the city's New Year's Eve celebration, according to CNN affiliate WPMI.

entries.title: Storm drenching California leads to widespread flooding, water rescues and power outages
entries.description: Northern California was inundated with widespread flooding and power outages as a powerful atmospheric river barreled into the region, forcing water rescues, several highway closures, evacuation warnings and shelter-in-place orders.

entries.title: Three NYPD officers injured in machete attack near New Year's Eve celebration in Times Square, officials say
entries.description: Three New York City police officers are in stable condition after being struck by a man wielding a machete in an unprovoked attack near Times Square, according to the NYPD commissioner.

entries.title: Myths and facts about treating a hangover
entries.description: Are you celebrating the first day of 2023 with a hangover?

entries.title: Europe's big question: What a diminished Russia will do next
entries.description: Russia's war in Ukraine has proven almost every assumption wrong, and left Europe wondering what left is safe to assume.

entries.title: Colorado library closes due to meth contamination
entries.description: Boulder, Colorado, has closed its main public library due to methamphetamine contamination in the facility's bathrooms and some seating areas, city officials say.

entries.title: TSA finds gun parts hidden in peanut butter jars at JFK Airport
entries.description: A traveler at New York City's John F. Kennedy International airport got into a sticky situation -- literally.

entries.title: Anita Pointer of The Pointer Sisters dies, 74
entries.description: Anita Pointer, one of the founding members of the R&B group The Pointer Sisters, has died at age 74, according to her publicist Roger Neal.

entries.title: Where to travel in 2023: The best destinations to visit
entries.description: New year equals new outlook. Apply this formula liberally to travel planning in 2023.

entries.title: Alabama airport worker dies on ramp in incident involving jet
entries.description: A worker at the Montgomery Regional Airport in Alabama died Saturday in an incident on the ramp, the Federal Aviation Administration said Saturday.

entries.title: Taiwan willing to offer help to China to deal with Covid-19 surge
entries.description: Taiwan's President Tsai Ing-wen said the self-ruled democratic island is willing to provide assistance to help China deal with its Covid surge after Beijing eased its hardline approach last month.

entries.title: Kim Jong Un calls for exponential increase in North Korea's nuclear arsenal amid threats from South, US
entries.description: North Korean leader Kim Jong Un is calling for an "exponential increase" in his country's nuclear weapons arsenal as threats from South Korea and the Untied States increase, Pyongyang's state media reported Sunday.

entries.title: See adorable photo of Anderson's son and Andy's son mimicking their dads on set
entries.description: Anderson Cooper and Andy Cohen share updates on how their families have grown over the past year.
